RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN WARRIOR was settled then rallied five wide into the turn, was six wide at the top of the stretch and then lugged in and was in a strong drive to drew away in late stretch. TOOMANYNAMES was stalking the pace while two wide into the turn, rallied and moved out to be three wide for the stretch drive, was gaining ground and was second best. SKI CAT dueled for the lead while inside, was in a long drive but weakened in late stretch. PROFESSIONAL GRADE was settled while two wide into the turn, was blocked behind a wall of horses then split rivals in mid stretch and was gaining ground in late stretch. TOUCHDOWN OKLAHOMA chased the early pace while three wide into the turn, was in a long drive but faltered in late stretch. IMA FUN GUY chased the early pace while inside, saved ground on the turn then lacked a rally when needed. ONE LUCKY BOY was allowed to settled then raced three wide into the turn then failed to menace. WRECK IT was unhurried early and inside on the turn but was no threat. I CONDUIT chased the early pace while two wide, was used up then gave way. CINCO MAJESTIC chased the early pace while three wide into the turn, dropped back when entering the stretch drive.
